The Withered Depths lie within the Forest of Confusion. Trees grow impossibly tall and twisted, bark blackened with fungal rot.
This blight is not natural. It is an orphaned experiment.

The Spirebound Conclave's Prism Thesis faction implanted resonance crystals in old-growth root systems, attempting to merge plant matter with preservation magic.
When supply routes collapsed, the Conclave never retrieved the crystals.

Without calibration, crystal matrices pulsed in feedback loops, warping surrounding ecology over centuries.
Root systems fused into labyrinthine underground networks. Fungal colonies absorbed preservation enchantments, gaining crude directed growth.
Trees that should have died persisted in animate rot, magically prevented from completing their natural cycle.

A druidic order attempted containment. Their confusion mists were quarantine for the crystal resonance, not protection from outsiders.
The druids died demographically: their tradition required decades of apprenticeship that recruitment could not supply.
The last generation fell at their posts, bodies preserved by the same resonance they opposed.

At the corruption's heart sits the Blightmother: a living organism merged with mineral structure, grown to monstrous scale without oversight. A custodial entity with no master and no stop condition.

Guilt chain: Midgaard's sealed warrants supplied laborers to the Conclave. The Conclave's experiments created the blight. The blight now threatens trade routes the city depends on.
